README for libjpeg-turbo


OVERLAY NOTES

The upstream build fails to link its own test/utility binaries (tjunittest,
tjcomp, tjdecomp, tjtran): they link only against libturbojpeg.so, which
itself needs __fpclassifyf (glibc's backing symbol for the fpclassify()
macro on floats, part of libm, not libc). Since these targets don't link
-lm explicitly and the linker here doesn't resolve transitive shared-library
dependencies automatically, __fpclassifyf is left undefined.

This overlay adds -lm globally via LDFLAGS instead of patching each
target_link_libraries() call in CMakeLists.txt individually -- simpler and
harmless, since linking libm unnecessarily has no downside.
